Description: Blueprint Advisory offers Salesforce consulting, software development, and business advisory services.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Chicago Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Blueprint Advisory is a Salesforce product development outsourcer (PDO) and system integrator (SI). We provide startups, enterprise companies, and global product managers the trusted expertise that can only be learned in the trenches building successful software products from the ground up. The core leadership team at Blueprint was previously responsible for creating, scaling, and ultimately exiting a company called Talent Rover.  Blueprint's CEO, Brandon Metcalf, founded Talent Rover in 2010, leveraging the Salesforce platform to create a staffing and recruitment software application focused on the sales-to-invoice customer journey.  It quickly grew to eight global offices and went on to become the 9th fastest-growing software company in America (Inc.500) in 2017, before being acquired by Bullhorn in 2018 and becoming an integral part in the company's all-in-one sales and recruitment cloud-based solution. Through Talent Rover's explosive growth and acclaimed startup journey, a select group of the company's leadership team saw firsthand the wide range of obstacles and challenges software companies face when developing Salesforce solutions and bringing new products to market.  Leveraging nearly a decade of lessons learned building Talent Rover from idea to exit, Blueprint Advisory provides companies of all sizes with the kind of expertise that can only be gained building a world-class global software company.

Full Description: The Golden Gate Bridge is a suspension bridge spanning the Golden Gate strait, a channel between San Francisco Bay and the Pacific Ocean. It is anchored by twin towers that reach skyward 746 feet. To support the suspended roadway, two cables, each more than 7,000 feet in length and both containing 80,000 miles of wire stretch over the top of the towers and are rooted in concrete anchorages on shore. Pedestrians including wheelchair users and bicyclists can go on the sidewalks of the bridge during daylight hours but roller blades, skateboards, and roller skates are not permitted. There are vista points on both north and south sides of the bridge with parking lots. The Golden Gate Bridge was officially opened on May 27, 1937, and is operated by The Golden Gate Bridge, Highway and Transportation District, a special district of the State of California formed in 1928.

GlycoFibers also have applications as therapies for a range of microbiome related diseases.  Renewables: Midori's Breaking the Biomass Barrier™ technology melts and digests biomass into sugars with a solid, recyclable catalyst at low-cost. Applications for low-cost sugar production include biofuels production and industrial chemicals fermentation feed. Midori's catalyst also converts sugars into high-value chemicals which can serve as intermediates for a range of formerly petroleum-derived substances, including plastics.

Full Description: Praxis History and Values Praxis Consulting Group, Inc. was founded in Philadelphia in 1995 by two of our principals, Ginny Vanderslice and Alex Moss. Initially we provided communication, training and organizational development services primarily to employee-owned companies. While we continue to work extensively with employee-owned companies, our practice has expanded to include work with nonprofits, socially responsible businesses and other organizations interested in developing workplace cultures that maximize employee engagement and responsibility. With the addition of consultants, Praxis has broadened its services to include: leadership development, coaching, union-management partnerships, process improvement strategies, strategic planning, governance, and conflict management.  Over the past fifteen years, Praxis has grown to include ten staff members, who together have backgrounds in a range of disciplines, including: organizational development, social psychology, adult education, business management, and finance.  We believe in the importance of giving back to the community. We do this by donating a portion of our profits each year to a selected nonprofit organization. We also provide some services on a pro bono basis to organizations in need, and we encourage staff to become actively involved in community organizations. In 2007, Praxis became a founding B Corporation, one of hundreds of companies across the country whose commitment to Triple Bottom line values (people, planet, and profits) is recognized via a stringent, third-party administered certification process.
